{:metadata {:description [{"text" "<p>Von Willebrand factor (VWF) is a multimeric adhesive protein involved in the initiation and progression of thrombus formation at sites of vascular injury [[cite:PUB00016077]]. VWF allows platelets to adhere to sites of vascular injury, forming a bridge between the sub-endothelial collagen matrix and the platelet-surface receptor complex GPIb-IX-V [[cite:PUB00087266]].  VWF is also a chaperone for coagulation factor VIII, delivering it to the injury site and protecting it from clearance from the plasma [[cite:PUB00087263]].  The protein is multidomain with four VWFD domains, four TIL domains, three VWFA domains, three VWFC domains and a C-terminal CTCK domain [[cite:PUB00087264]].  VWF is cleaved to release von Willebrand antigen 2 by a furin-like endopeptidase [[cite:PUB00087267]].  Von Willebrand diseases 1, 2 and 3 are deficiencies of VWF, resulting in impaired platelet aggregation and prolonged bleeding after trauma [[cite:PUB00087265]].  Von Willebrand disease 3 results in haemophilia.</p>", "llm" false, "checked" false, "updated" false}], :is-reviewed-llm false, :representative-structure nil, :overlaps-with nil, :member-databases {"pirsf" {"PIRSF002495" "von Willebrand factor"}}, :is-updated-llm false, :name {"name" "Von Willebrand factor", "short" "Von_Willebrand_factor"}, :wikipedia nil, :source-database "interpro", :type "family", :counters {"structures" 0, "domain_architectures" 0, "proteomes" 101, "taxa" 376, "subfamilies" 0, "interactions" 0, "matches" 256, "sets" 0, "proteins" 226, "structural_models" {"alphafold" 0}, "pathways" 41}, :integrated nil, :cross-references {}, :set-info nil, :accession "IPR037578", :literature {"PUB00087264" {"URL" nil, "issue" "2", "authors" ["Zhou YF" "Eng ET" "Zhu J" "Lu C" "Walz T" "Springer TA."], "ISO_journal" "Blood", "DOI_URL" "https://doi.org/10.1182/blood-2012-01-405134", "medline_journal" "Blood", "title" "Sequence and structure relationships within von Willebrand factor.", "ye